{
  "explanation": "The defendant, acting as an accountant, abused a significant position of trust to embezzle $25,000 from their employer. This breach of fiduciary duty is a serious offense that damages business security. However, several mitigating factors are present: the defendant has no prior criminal history, the funds were used to address personal debts rather than to finance a luxurious lifestyle, and the defendant has demonstrated remorse by making a good-faith effort to partially repay the stolen money. A balancing of these factors—specifically the abuse of trust versus the lack of criminal history and partial restitution—warrants a brief period of incarceration to serve as a deterrent, followed by probation and a structured plan to complete full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
